      "blockType": "text",
      "semanticType": "Body",
      "text": "The Access Control (AC) family manages authorization and restriction of system access to authenticated users, processes, and devices. [1] Controls in this family address account management, access enforcement, information flow, and the separation of duties between privileged and non-privileged roles. Implementation responsibility is shared between the organization (O) and the system or service (S); selected controls are designated O/S where both parties contribute.",
      "confidence": 0.8999999761581421,
      "cascadeTrail": [
        {
          "tier": "T0",
          "tierName": "classify_blocks",
          "disposition": "accept",
          "confidence": 0.8999999761581421
        }
      ]
