      "blockType": "text",
      "semanticType": "Body",
      "text": "Discussion: Examples of system account types include individual, shared, group, system, guest or anonymous, emergency, developer, temporary, and service. Account monitoring can be modeled as a Bernoulli detection process where the probability of detecting at least one anomalous event over n independent observations is given by Equation C.1: [2]",
      "confidence": 0,
      "cascadeTrail": [
        {
          "tier": "T0",
          "tierName": "classify_blocks",
          "disposition": "accept",
          "confidence": 0
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "p0_e13",
      "page": 0,
      "bbox": [
        0.0847058826022678,
        0.44252526639687895,
        1,
        0.5309091047807173
      ],
      "blockType": "text",
      "semanticType": "Body",
      "text": "P_detect = 1 - (1 - p)^n (C.1) where p is the per-observation detection probability and n is the number of independent observations within the monitoring window. Related Controls: AC-3, AC-5, AC-6, AC-17, AC-20, AU-2, AU-12, IA-2, IA-4, IA-5, IA-8, MA-3, MA-5, PE-2, PL-4, PS-2, PS-4, PS-5, PS-7, SC-7, SC-12, SC-13, SC-37.",
      "confidence": 0,
      "cascadeTrail": [
        {
          "tier": "T0",
          "tierName": "classify_blocks",
          "disposition": "accept",
          "confidence": 0
        }
